# Agmsg Lanes

Use this when the project enables Agmsg.

Workspace rule source:

- `..\..\System\docs\agmsg.md`
- `..\..\System\docs\agent-roles.md`
- `..\..\System\docs\services.md`

## Lane Contract

- Agmsg carries short pointers, ACKs, status, and artifact paths.
- GitHub remains the official source of truth after publication.
- Do not put secrets, raw credentials, browser state, or long transcripts in
  Agmsg.
- Use `required_reply=answer` only when a human or lane session is expected to
  consume the inbox during the milestone.

## Smoke

From the Tools root:

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\System\scripts\agmsg-console.ps1 -NoConsume
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\System\scripts\agmsg-trace.ps1 -CorrelationId <id>
```

Record the result in the project issue or milestone report.
